reviews: Staff was friendly and helpful. They gave us some great suggestions. The shower leaked and water was on the floor outside after taking a shower but the shower control was amazing. FIrst time I have seen such a device. The room was small.

This hotel has an ideal location with regard to many aspects. The staff was very friendly and helpful, the room was clean and very pleasantly designed. Taking into account the enormous price of almost € 300 per night, however, I feel that the room could have been a little more spacious or could at least have provided some more space to stow suitcases and to store or hang up clothes.

Lovely hotel just a short walk from Gare Austerlitz and or the metro station. We received a very warm welcome on arrival and by luck our room was ready. The room was quite large by Paris standards and very clean. We had the breakfast which was good value and plentiful and good quality too. There is a bus stop right outside the hotel which is in a really nice area. Really friendly and professional staff.

Our stay in Paris couldn't have been better. The hotel was small (42 rooms) but cozy with everything you needed. Great testy breakfast to start the day. Hotel staff (specially Emma) was very helpful advising us for trips and places to visit. Room was small but this is Paris. Room was clean and had everything we could need. Located close to two METRO stations and bus services across the street We will book this hotel in our next visit to Paris..

We were very pleased with this accommodation! The area was close to the Latin Quarter. Our room was very clean and we had a small balcony. It was small but enough space for 2 people.There were many excellent restaurants a short walk away and the tourist areas were reached easily by bus or train. The bus stop was about a half block and the train station was an easy walk. We had the option of a continental breakfast or a full English breakfast for an extra amount. The breakfast was very good. We would highly recommend this hotel.

This hotel is in a great location in Paris and felt safe. It is near to the metro stops, has restaurants near by. The Hotel itself was exceptionally clean, fabulous to come back each day to fresh towels and our beds fully made. Comfortable beds. We were in room 302 and the only downside was, it was quite noisy at night. Lovely friendly hotel staff. We didn't have breakfast, but, there is a cafe with the most delicious fresh pastries right across the road. Recommend this hotel to friends and family

I was very favourably impressed by the modern room fitout, comfortable bedding, standard of cleaning, and closeness to many Metro stops.

The only downsides for me were that there was a lot of noise coming from the stairwell, and that the room was small with poor luggage space etc. Otherwise - lovely.

The room was amazing. Very clean, Great views, bed was comfy. We had the best stay here. Room was very quiet so if you are jetlaged and want to sleep in, best place ever! Food was great and the staff was beyond nice! My first time in Paris was great and partly due to staying at this hotel 10/10 all around!

An excellent hotel with top class staff. Breakfast had hot and cold food and drinks of a high standard and the staff were welcoming and friendly. This hotel is in a great location to visit Paris with many locations being within walking distance. Highly recommended.

We had a 'mini suite' (2 adults 2 kids) in this nice small hotel. Double room was clean. Separate toilet but shower was in bath tub. Personnel is friendly and always present. Breakfast was very good. I liked the hotel because it was not anonymous. It is well located with many restaurants nearby and good access to the centre. For 30eur day you can park the car in private garage 50m away.

Excellent service and value and a truly good sized, comfortable room, larger than most without costing SO much more, in a city where a cupboard is commonly considered the standard. Convenient location close to public transport and walkable to many points of interest.

Excellent hotel in a great location, close to metros and bus routes
Lots of restaurants and shops within walking distance. The hotel room was spacious (for Paris) and priced reasonably - the staff were very welcoming and friendly.
Would highly recommend

The hotel was groat for our short stay. Check in/out was easy. The hotel must have recently remodeled the bathroom and the water pressure was above my expectations. Keep in mind the hotel is a bit far away from some attractions. We had no problems walking to Norte Dame but any further and you might want to consider public transport. Head to the Les Gobelins stop and the train takes you directly in to town.

We enjoyed our stay. The rooms were comfortable, good beds. Customer service really friendly and helpful. We had a sauna which we enjoyed too. Thank you. We didn't try the breakfast, we went over the road instead. Overall very good.

Perfect for a short stay in Paris. Close to metro. Clean rooms. Very nice and friendly staff. Room on backyard is very quiet, no noise at all. The one thing i did not expect was the 11 € charged to keep my luggage for half an hour.

After looking through numerous reviews I finally booked this hotel and didn’t regret it!
Upon arrival the reception were very friendly unlike other experiences in Paris. We were located in Room 504 which was spotless, included a shower and bath tub. Not to mention the beautiful balcony with the Eiffel Tower view!
The hotel includes a spa and gym but given only 2 nights in Paris we didn’t end up using it.
It is situated nearby many cafes and shops which is ideal and the Grande Mosque is just a 7minute walk!
Definitely worth visiting and would highly recommend :)

We stayed two nights at Demeure and found it had a boutique vibe. Cozy and comfortable. The room was a junior suite and quite sizable by French standards. The bathroom had a separate toilet compartment and a towel warmer, both of which were a welcome surprise, however, the tub could use a larger screen to keep water from splashing all over while bathing. Overall a very pleasant stay.

A very elegant hotel, comfortable, immaculate rooms and friendly staff. It is ideally situated, close to buses and the Metro. It is within walking distance of the Pantheon and Notre Dame. We enjoyed our stay here very much.

A brilliant experience, we booked this hotel for two nights following our stay at Disneyland Paris. We had booked a junior suite, it was great. It gave proper Parisian vibes. The location of the hotel is great, lots of cafes. Halal food variety. Also very safe to walk around at night compared to other areas.

Metro is close by so you can explore the rest of Paris. The staff are brilliant too.. especially Khalid who gave my daughter a teddy bear which made her day. We used the spa which was also very relaxing.

Overall a great stay and wouldn’t mind staying here again.

Thoroughly enjoyed our stay here over the weekend, especially with Ireland beating France on Saturday!
Room very clean and quiet Breakfast was very good and the staff could not have been more accommodating No restaurant on the premises but the recommendations from the staff were tremendous

Loved this hotel so much. They were so kind and provided us with everything we needed. Me and my girlfriend loved the hot chocolate and candy in the lobby!! It was so yummy. The sauna was so nice too. Also, Saifeddin was super helpful and accommodating for us! Appreciate him helping us and giving us tips.

Great services in a confortable hôtel located in an amazing environment full of activities and curiosities!
The hotel has interesting access to the parking of Le jardin des Plantes!
Great restaurant at proximity

Nice hotel in a lovely district of Paris - lots of lovely shops and restaurants in this area - which is part residential / part touristy. We had a very comfortable stay - our room was on the 5th floor with great views across Paris. The hotel staff were very friendly and helpful and nothing was too much trouble.

This is the smallest room we’ve ever been in in Paris. There’s literally no space to walk and we have to squeeze through the room to go from the WC to the sink. The bathroom is really tiny as well and the floor area is smaller than a normal sized bath towel!!

Everithing Was good ,perfect position for visiting Paris duriing our stay for the end of 2022.
The only problem was a signal of alarm for smoking at 4 o clock in the morning but this is not a hotel’s fault!

The location was great, the service top level. Clean room, comfortable bad, coffe machine and filter water in the room for free. The hotel will be a best choice for your stay. Close to gare de Lyon.
The service on the reception desk was very helpful and looking after what you need.

Recently stayed here with my family for a short city break, the hotel is clean, the standard rooms are kind of small however we upgraded for a good price and the other room was great, the location is great plenty of restaurants and shops around and a great coffee shop (Crible) near by. The hotel has parking just 2 minutes away which is great and it’s secure. The staff at the hotel are very polite and helpful and go beyond to help you, I would recommend and would stay here again.

I won’t bore you with “he said, she said”, but let’s be clear: a person working a reception desk should be, above all, receptive. Whether it is lack of training, extreme job dissatisfaction, or simply having a bad day, the woman in charge of checking people wins the title for the worst service I’ve experienced in 20 years of international travel. Condescending, sharp-tongued, and lazy. A brilliant combination for guests to experience. So outrageous, her boss offered to send up champagne as an apology. It never arrived. I travel to paris often, but will not stay in this hotel again. Small rooms in paris are normal (as this hotel offers), but small minded employees who clearly hate their job is not to be tolerated.

Stayed here for 2 nights, and was pleasantly surprised with the quality of the hotel. We didn’t eat there, but the rooms were lovely, and all the reception staff were very friendly. The location was good. As only a 5 min walk from metro, and about 10/15 mins to the lively areas.

The Amazing staff went above and beyond to cater to our needs, the clean tidy rooms were nicely styled and bathrooms were nice , with comfortable beds and great location to local shops and dining 10/10 would stay again!

I cannot recommend this hotel enough. Staff are welcoming and friendly and great with kids. The whole team work hard to provide a great time. Room was always cleaned daily and reception staff so helpful to ensure the trip runs smoothly. Close to metro, a supermarket and lots lovely eating places. I would def stay again nothing was ever too much trouble thank you

The hotel la Demeure is a small character hotel on Boul St Marcel bordering on the Latin Quarters east side. The rooms and common areas have been modernized and are clean and comfortable. The location is close to the metro and on a main bus route that traverses all the tours areas.All the amenities are within a block- patisserie, markets, cafes and restaurants.

The reception staff were very friendly and helpful and we thoroughly enjoyed our stay. Our room was on the 6th floor with great views across Paris. It was very clean and comfortable with a great shower. This district of Paris is very nice with lots of neighbourhood cafes, restaurants, shops and interesting streets and we will certainly return again.

Rooms were very clean and staff were incredibly nice. Front desk went above and beyond by reserving a taxi for us so that we wouldn’t be late for our flight early the next morning. Although the room was a little tight, it’s pretty common. Bathroom looked recently updated.

Very nice atmosphere in the whole hotel. Kind staff that helps you with everything and even take the time to make a joke :)
When we arrived way too early the room wasn't ready yet, but it was no problem to leave our luggage. The check-in was smooth. The room itself was brand new, very clean and had everything we needed.
Would definitely recommend!

We had a lovely 5 day stay. Hotel staff were friendly & helpful. Room was perfect for our family. Air conditioning was excellent given very hot weather. Buffet breakfast beautiful. This area is a perfect base for site seeing with the bus just outside the hotel & shops/restaurants in the local area.

Overall I had a good stay at the hotel. The room was nice and clean, comfortable bed and good bathroom. Workout facility did the job. Nice neighborhood with lots of restaurants of varying cuisine away from the hustle and bustle of downtown but still close enough to it.

Only complaints are you have to ask the front desk to adjust the temperature in your room. As a US based chain I was disappointed they don't have universal power outlets in the rooms.

Staff was very polite and welcoming! i was very impressed by the quality of services provided by the staff and the 2 gentlemen working at the reception during my stay but a rooms are a bit overpriced. Hotel was clean and room were clean.

We travelled as a couple for a 2-night weekend away. This hotel has a great location, lovely staff and nicely renovated hotel. The room was very small though - I had expected this from reading previous reviews, so had booked a "superior double room with relaxation space" but cannot imagine where the relaxation space was meant to be - the desk (though this was snug against the bed once sitting)? or the balcony (though not relaxing with the street noise and weather and nowhere to sit)? I even wondered if we were in a classic suite (queried with front desk, nope). 4 stars are credit to the staff and the amazing location with lots of lovely restaurants, cafes, markets, metro and bus stations. Hotel has great sauna and gym, we didnt try the breakfast (lots of boulangeries nearby) but it looked good. We would stay again, but would have to be prepared to book a suite

Our "classic room" on the 6th floor was spacious & lovely--except we had no hot water in the tub/shower and the bed needs a new mattress. A/C worked fine, even with the heat wave. Breakfast was more than adequate, with excellent coffee.

Hotel is nice and clean. Good breakfast. Hotel is located in quite area, close to metro station. Many bistros and shops around. Hotel room for family with 2 children could be a bit bigger for more comfort. I recommend this hotel.

I can only recommend this small but very friendly hotel.
The rooms are nice and very clean. I enjoyed the continental breakfast very much.
Bars and restaurant, bus and metro station are in the neighborhood

We stayed at this hotel for 6 nights, as a group of 4 in two seperate rooms. The staff did everything possible to accomodate all of our requests, called us taxi’s and gave helpful suggestions. Super friendly and couldn’t recommend staying here more.

This is a very well located hotel, clean with attentive and polite staff. However, the rooms are too small. There was no cupboard, just a dusty curtain in front of a rail and almost no space to get around the bed (so not a space to relax in).

The hotel is cozy, very clean, and has great amenities. The staff gives you a great customer service. Also, is located close to restaurants, coffee shops, etc. I loved staying there! I definitely recommend it!

My stay was short business trip but with many things I had to address. This was helped by the support I received from the tremendous Hotel staff, nothing was too much trouble. The Hotel itself is smart with a modern interior but still classy in its own right. I will stay here again if I return to Paris.

The hotel was conveniently located and the staff was very welcoming. Overall we had a great stay! The only point that could be improved was the room which temperature which was too warm. A/C could not switched on in May.

We had a very pleasant stay at this hotel. Service was great as was the room. Nice decor, good bed and nice view. Nice services like wellness and fitness available and well equipped. We will come back when we plan our next visit to Paris! Three nights was to short…

Best Western did not disappoint us. We are BW members and we are happy to have chosen BW La Demeure for its excellent quality service and cleanliness. Breakfast was great and the staff were superb from the front reception to the cleaners and the kitchen staff. Great job! Thank you for making our stay a memorable one!

Amazing staff. With some problems with our baggage at the airport we recieved a lot of help from the staff at the hotel. Desk agent Ismael mad a lot of phonecalls to help us to locate and to make sure that we would get our baggage back. The service was really suberb.

We (2 adults and 2 young children) stayed in a junior suite for two nights following a busy Disneyland holiday. Our suite was spacious with a large comfortable bed and generous pull out sofa. The rooms were spotless and very calming. Lots of lighting options, large soft towels, good coffee machine and complementary teddies for the children all lent to a great stay. The breakfast was excellent and the staff we met were all very friendly. The location of the hotel was perfect for us as we explored the Jardin des plantes and the latin quarter on foot, and the Eiffel tower was an easy metro journey away. We will not hesitate to book again. Thank you again for a wonderful stay.

The hotel has a great location, ideal to reach several tourist places directly by walk and plenty of places to lunch or dinner; it's very well connected with public transport lines. Personnel is amazing and always willing to help. The room, despite a bit small, is always very clean and comfortable

From communication before arrival to check out: this hotel offers charming, welcoming venue where quality is outstanding. Decorative and comfortable & cosy rooms. Professional fitness, sauna and in everything else going the extra mile to make guests feel at home.

I really enjoyed staying here. Friendly, helpful staff. Very clean and comfortable room. Internet had a super strong signal. It’s a little outside of the touristy areas, but just a couple blocks from Metro or still within walking distance to sites such as Notre Dame & Maubert market.

We stayed at the hotel for a week. Excellent and friendly service at the front desk, all very helpful in providing directions and advice on where we could do our covid tests. The room was comfortable and clean, a little small but still OK size by Parisian standards. Bathroom is a little tight but shower and hot water worked really well which was very important for me. Overall an very enjoyable stay.

When I was just arrived, I was obliged to leave a caution of 50 €, for "any service you can get and not pay". I was really offended by this request, and it is the first time I hear of this. It seems to me offensive for any customer of high -level hotels, especially in a room with no fridge!
Moreover, the role of the concierge seems to be unuseful, if he doesn't know that the lift is not working and he doesn't advice customers living at the second floor

Its my first time in Paris and I stayed at Best Western Plus La Demeure and staying at this hotel helped me enjoyed my stay in Paris even more. The hotel receptionist (specifically Leo) is very friendly and accommodating, making sure that have everything I need and that I feel really welcome. He is very hospitable and speaks english really well. The rooms are really clean and the design gives you a Parisian vibes. I got even surprise that you can book the sauna privately for yourself and have a good massage. I will definitely recommend staying at this place. The price is also reasonable and pretty cheap for the quality you can get. Thumbs up!

We stayed for one night. It was very close to the metro, only a 6 minute walk. The staff was friendly and the room was great and specious with a lovely view. We will definitely come back here when in Paris

Staff very helpful and room was clean with a comfy bed, but very small. The bathroom only had space to stand in one spot on the floor, very difficult to easily shower/dress. We didn't have breakfast but it looked good.

We stayed in Junior Suite and no complaints. The room is clean and good enough for 4 people to stay. Staff are friendly . The hotel is centrally located and walking distance to the metro station . There are nearby good restaurants to dine . Will definitely use this hotel upon my return.

Average hotel in Paris. The hotel is a renovated apartment building with tight halls. The junior suite did not have a fridge. Overall clean room. Location was good, calm area. A bit over priced compared to the standard. The parking was around 800m away.

Rooms were tiny. but that's probably to be expected in a city hotel at this price level.

What drove me NUTS though was the piano in the little lounge adjacent to reception. Twice when I wanted to sit in the reception area - work and talk to friends/colleagues, someone was having fun with the piano.

In both instances, someone was practicing - both piano and singing and THEY were having a fabulous time. That's fine - but I had no option but to listen to loud (and not very good) singing and playing - nowhere else to go - and again, it was LOUD!

I'm not sure that the balance of one or two people having fun while everyone else just has to listen is right and think they should put the piano somewhere more isolated, get rid of it - or have one with headphones so others can live/drink in peace.

My daughter and I stayed in this lovely hotel and it was everything I’d hoped for. I was prepared for the room to be small, and it was, it being Paris, but it was thoughtfully designed and beautifully decorated, so that it wasn’t an inconvenience.

The bed and pillows were so comfortable, I wished I could take them home with me, and the shower luxurious even while small.

The staff was so friendly and helpful, particularly one young man, my favorite concierge, who’s name I wish I’d thought to get. He helped us find Covid tests at the last second when I was in a panic, asked how we’d faired when we returned, and wished us a safe trip. I arranged a taxi to the airport ahead of time for early morning and it arrived without a hitch. We also booked a tour through their website which was wonderful.

The hotel is quiet and in a beautiful neighborhood within easy walking distance to public transportation, restaurants, and shops.

We highly recommend this fine hotel.

I particularly liked the push-button rain shower, which worked perfectly every time. The breakfast was always perfect. I needed a bigger desk for work, and the staff were helpful in bringing a second table. From this larger desk I had a long view of the Eiffel Tower! (I was on the sixth floor - not every room would have that view, but I certainly enjoyed it.)

Great hotel, staff is friendly and helpful. Nice location, close to several metro stations, lots of restaurants in the area.
We wanted a room on a higher floor then the one provided. Sophie was amazing accommodating our request, and we ended up getting a room with a nice view.

Frendly Service, Special thanks to Le Specjał thanks to Leo. Tasty breakfast. Kind atmosphere. Comfortable beed, nice design. Recently renovated.
No sink in the toalet, and cold Scrambled eggs on breakfast, that was the only inconvenience.

One of the best hotels me and my boyfriend have been to. Super clean and modern rooms for a great price. The staff at the front desk were all so nice!! Would definitely go here again next time we go to Paris :)

Very nice days in this Hotel. Short distances to the Metro (3-4 min.) and Bus Station( near the Hotel). We prefered to walk in Paris so we reached the seigtseinngs in aprox. 45 -55 min.
The room is clean. The beed is comfortable. The staff at the reception was always very helpfull and profesional.
Good locations to eat and drink something in the neighberhood.

Excellent restful stay after a long flight from the US. The staff is courteous and welcoming, the breakfast is scrumptious, the room is very clean and comfortable. I will definitely make it my Paris stay when I come back.

We had a wonderful stay. We stayed one night. The kids in the room next to ours and friends of ours across the hall. Nice that we were placed next to each other. I told the lady at the front desk that it was my wife’s birthday and when we later arrived in our room there was a little bottle of champagne waiting for us with a card from the staff. Really nice. The hotel is perfectly situated. Clean room nicely decorated and wonderful bed.

Good location, near the Austerlitz station, and plenty of small restaurants.
Friendly staff, both at reception and breakfast. Quiet room, even on the first floor, boulevard side. Dog friendly. Value for money.

We had an amazing stay at Best Western Plus La Demeure. When we arrived we first got a room with at the third floor with a view to the garden. However when we asked the staff if it was possible to switch rooms, they were so nice and switched us immediatly to a room with city view on the fifth floor! Overall we had a very pleasent stay and the staff helped us with every little thing. Would definitly recommend and looking forward to get back as soon as possible!

Nice, cosy, well situated. We booked two rooms for a family of four (two adults + 2 children), but the allotted rooms were in two different floors. The lift was out of order. The rooms were nice and clean but really small, without wardrobes. The bath was also nice but small.

The superior twin room was a good accommodation per us and the people professional. But the last day there was a trouble with the lift. So we went up and down on the stairs even with the baggages. The room was located at the fourth and we are not young people ...

Had a wonderful couple of days here. very peaceful and pleasant part of town and not too far from the center. The hotel staff are most helpful and courteous. The room was a little on the small side but not too small.

We really enjoyed our stay in your hotel. Your front desk service was very nice and good, the room was - although maybe somewhat small - excellent in cleanliness, finish, and facilities, and the location is conveniently close to metro stations. We would definitely come back to this place!

I went on vacation with my boy-friend, the hotel is amazing and the staff is really lovely, definetely we’ll come back, I advise it to everybody, the rooms are comfortable and with a wonderful view of Paris

A 2 day trip to Paris for me & my daughter so it was very important to have a good hotel in a nice location, close to the Metro and plenty of restaurants nearby!! What an amazing hotel - from a super friendly receptionist who stored our bags as room was not ready (we arrived in the morning!!) and also booked our batobus (water taxi) tickets online (cheaper than at the kiosk) to a fabulous room with amazing views of the Eiffel Tower and a gorgeous little balcony with lights on - so pretty!! The room was lovely, bed was so comfortable and the shower amazing!!! The towels were super thick and even slippers were provided - essential for relaxing in after walking round Paris all day!!! We didn’t use the Spa as we were too tired but the staff were so attentive in letting us know it was available should we wish to use it!! The breakfast was lovely - gorgeous pancakes, mini pastries, fresh fruit, good coffee and juices! Cooked breakfast looked nice too and the waitress was really nice too!!

To sum it up - lovely hotel with very friendly and helpful staff and a great breakfast - 100% recommend and we will definitely return!!! Thank you for a great overnight stay!!!

Stayed here for Valentine's day all the facilities were lush I highly recommend this hotel if you are looking to completely relax. the Hotel staff were very welcoming anything we needed we were catered too. I was very lucky to have the top floor view and could see the Eiffel tower light show at night which was a bonus this was my first trip to Paris I would highly recommend! Thank you for our stay Le Demeure.

Staff were very friendly and accommodating. Always asked how we were and were there 24/7 if we needed anything. Hotel itself had everything we needed and good location for cafes, restaurants and local shops. Very close to metro and easy to get around. Room itself was quiet small but I noticed alot of hotels in Paris were like that. Very modern and room cleaned everyday. Could not fault.

The hotel was so nice, the staff was so helpful and the shower was amazing! I went by car and used it a lot, the area was super nice for this as well. The staff was so easygoing, and didn't act difficult or rude when I wanted a late check out. Definitely going to stay here more often when I go to paris. Very pleasantly left to go back home

This is a convenient and clean hotel, which was close to the venue of our meeting. The room was clean and and had all requirements. The room was a bit small though. Many restaurants nearby and a nice breakfast buffet.

I had just one night at the Best Western Plus La Demeure and everything was perfect! My room was very spacious and the breakfast very fresh and delicious with lots of options. It was my second time there and certainly not the last!

My stay at Best Western Plus La Demeure has been amazing and super comfortable. The hotel has everything you need to feel at home (great gym, big rooms, comfy bathroom, etc...)

I will definitely come back sooner than later.

I had the pleasure of staying here for 2 nights, and I must say this went very well. The room I stayed in was very small, however did the trick. Sticking to that theme, the bathroom is also quite small, but still adequate. What really pushed it over the line was the shower, which was very nice especially considering I’m quite tall.

The staff is very nice but not accommodating. Rooms were cozy and clean at check in. My room had a great view of the city.
Housekeeping did not change my linens and my stay was 6 nights.
The elevator was out of service a few hours after I checked in and was not repaired until it was time for me to check out. My room was on the 6th floor and they did not offer to move me to a lower floor.
Some of the people staying there left because they simply could not climb the stairs multiple times a day. I would’ve left also if I would’ve received a full refund.

Wonderful stay on nye. Great views. Lovely staff and very helpful. Clean room and lovely shower. Would be good if breakfast was included but great location and lots to do. Very close to the Louvre which is one quick bus ride away

Location of the hotel is excellent, very close to all the main sites. Good places to eat nearby. The neighborhood was safe to walk late at night. The staff was amazing all along and was very attentive. Great rooms and views from the hotel to the Eiffel Tower. Would definitely recommend to stay here and would also stay here again!

The hotel is on the edge of the Latin Quarter and within walking distance to Notre Dame. The junior suite worked well for 2 couples and was both roomy and nicely appointed. The reception room and sitting rooms in the lobby were very nice, too. We did the full breakfast which was so convenient. Loved everything about this place!

This was our final hotel for our 3 week trip to Europe. We had a junior for the 4 of us and it was very spacious and comfortable. Front desk staff extremely helpful - got us a car for return trip to airport and made sure that all was confirmed. Paris is a very large city and this location is close to Notre Dame, but not to any other sites. You can walk to the Dame and catch a hop on hop off for touring. Lots of subways - but there was a strike while we were there so not sure if they would have helped.

Breakfast was plentiful and delicious. Would recommend this hotel.

We had a very pleasant stay at La Demeure. Refurbished and clean room, very friendly staff and large double bed. Our room was even upgraded to a superior one. Totally worth its price, can just recommend.

Excellent hotel: very clean, very well managed. Rooms are small but very comfortable. The breakfast in 2 forms covering the whole morning is an excellent idea! The location is central, with many restaurants, shops attractions within 15 mins walk. There are also larger rooms also appropriate for a small meeting work. The management is very friendly and helpful.

We stayed here on our first few nights in Paris and found it a great location with super friendly staff and ultra comfy beds. From here we walked most days to a number of great spots in Paris and enjoyed the local food the quarter had to offer.

Nice place and nice staff. Clean and well located. The room was really cute and the bathroom too. I would only change the fact that the gel they give has to be used as champoo too. Even this, I think is perfect.

Hotel is ideally located. You can go to Sorbonne university or Notre Dame etc. by foot. Breakfast is good, though it might be a little expensive (16€). The rooms are quite small but very tidy and clean. When you are tall, the bed length might be a challenge. You have to sleep diagonally.

We really loved our staying in La Demeure hotel ! The location is very good, the metro station is close and there are a lot of shops around the hotel as well. There is also a Carrefour market and a Boulangerie a few steps away which is important if you don’t want to pay extra for the hotel breakfast and a lot of restaurants and brasseries if you want to stay close by -the Korean restaurant right next to the hotel was AMAZING-. The room was very clean and though it is a standard small Parisian space, everything is very well thought out so you will not feel limited at all. The stuff was very friendly and ready to help and even gave us a complimentary bottle of champagne for my husband’s birthday! I only wish there was a small fridge in our room but it was not that important. I would stay again at this hotel and would also suggest it to anyone visiting Paris !

This hotel is a wee bit expensive but was absolutely worth it. Terrific rooms - Ideally positioned and the service was second to none. Great sleep and fantastic breakfast. The journey to & from Paris attractions was very easy via the Metro stations nearby.

The view from the 5th-floor rooms is fantastic. We have stayed in 504 and 505 previously and both can see the Eiffel Tower across the rooftops which is nice. Some rooms are very small, so if staying in a 'Classic' room then don't take too much with you! Lovely little breakfast room as well, with loads of restaurant choices all within a few minutes walk. You can also walk to Gare Austerlitz and the Natural History Museum and Gardens from here also.

The rooms are very complete. Unfortunately our room was very small, but everything you need is there. Location is okay. the possibility for parking is a big advantage.
Price and quality are in balance.

We had a very nice stay at La Demeure. The two of us spent 7 nights at the hotel. I loved the decor of the room, it had everything we needed including a safe and a little desk with a mirror which we used as a vanity to get ready. Situated in a quiet part of town, but under 5 a minute walk to many train lines which made it easy to explore all parts of the city.
